Subject: [PATCH 2/6] window-rule: extend disable-offscreen-frame-throttle to
 all windows

Previously, disable_offscreen_frame_throttle only applied to windows
being screen cast. Now it also applies to the ~1fps fallback timer for
any offscreen window, allowing specific windows to render at full rate
even when not on screen.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Haiku 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 CLAUDE.md   | 38 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 notes.txt   | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/niri.rs |  7 ++++++-
 3 files changed, 66 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 CLAUDE.md
 create mode 100644 notes.txt

diff --git a/CLAUDE.md b/CLAUDE.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..cd351791
--- /dev/null
+++ b/CLAUDE.md
@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@
+## Rule: always use qmd before reading files
+
+Before reading files or exploring directories, always use qmd to search for information in local projects.
+
+Available tools:
+
+- `qmd search "query"` — fast keyword search (BM25)
+
+- `qmd query "query"` — hybrid search with reranking (best quality)
+
+- `qmd vsearch "query"` — semantic vector search
+
+- `qmd get <file>` — retrieve a specific document
+
+Use qmd search for quick lookups and qmd query for complex questions.
+
+Use Read/Glob only if qmd doesn't return enough results.
+
+## After making code changes, update the index and regenerate embeddings:
+```bash
+qmd update
+qmd embed
+```
+
+## Gentoo packaging
+
+Changes are deployed to the system niri install via a Portage user patch.
+The patch is based on the `disable-offscreen-frame-throttle-v25.11` branch,
+which is rebased onto the `v25.11` tag to match `gui-wm/niri-25.11-r1`.
+
+After any changes to the v25.11 branch, remind the user to regenerate the patch and rebuild:
+
+```bash
+git -C ~/code/niri format-patch -1 disable-offscreen-frame-throttle-v25.11 --stdout | sudo tee /etc/portage/patches/gui-wm/niri/disable-offscreen-frame-throttle.patch
+sudo emerge -1 gui-wm/niri
+```
+
+The patch file lives at `/etc/portage/patches/gui-wm/niri/disable-offscreen-frame-throttle.patch`.
diff --git a/notes.txt b/notes.txt
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..9349571c
--- /dev/null
+++ b/notes.txt
@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@
+QMD Collection Setup
+====================
+
+Created a QMD collection for this repo using:
+
+    qmd collection add /home/sidney/code/niri --name niri --mask '**/*.{rs,toml,md,yml,yaml}'
+
+This indexes 224 files (Rust source, TOML configs, Markdown docs, and YAML files).
+
+The --mask flag sets the glob pattern (undocumented in the help text; found by inspecting the source).
+Default pattern is **/*.md — use --mask to override.
+
+To enable semantic/vector search, run:
+
+    qmd embed
+
+Useful search commands:
+
+    qmd search "keyword"              # fast BM25 keyword search
+    qmd query "natural language"      # hybrid search with reranking (best quality)
+    qmd vsearch "concept"             # vector/semantic search only
+    qmd search "something" -c niri    # scope to this collection
