From 8197eaf81c83dcedd00359b1404232d4e224b442 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sidney Hays <me@sidneyhays.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 23:54:11 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] window-rule: fix offscreen-frame-throttle-rate throttle
 being ignored

Pass |_, _| None as primary_scan_out_output in the offscreen throttle
send_frame calls so Smithay relies on the frame_overdue check (which
uses the throttle duration) rather than on_primary_scanout_output, which
short-circuits the throttle entirely when it returns Some(output).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/niri.rs | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/niri.rs b/src/niri.rs
index 0220a085..66564329 100644
--- a/src/niri.rs
+++ b/src/niri.rs
@@ -5078,7 +5078,7 @@ impl Niri {
                             output,
                             frame_callback_time,
                             Some(throttle),
-                            |_, _| Some(output.clone()),
+                            |_, _| None,
                         );
                     }
                 }
